reviews.headline: Holy Grail
reviews.comments: As someone who doesn't like a sticky gloss this is perfect for me and still gives me that shine that I'm looking for. I feel as though it competes with the bigger brands regarding hydration and shine! I will be purchasing again!

reviews.headline: best cheap gloss
reviews.comments: I have this product in several colors. It isn't sticky and glides on smoothly. Color lasts for a while but you'll need to reapply. It's so inexpensive!

reviews.headline: I wouldn't buy again
reviews.comments: This is like child lip gloss. It's shiny but doesn't add hydration. Reminds me of lip stick tbh. I have to use chapstick under neath this. And it doesn't last few minutes is all

reviews.headline: Must Buy!
reviews.comments: My fav, not too thick, goes on easily and lasts a long time

reviews.headline: Love this product!
reviews.comments: Love this product! It goes on so smoothly. I would definitely recommend this gloss to all my friends and family.

reviews.headline: Butter gloss
reviews.comments: Handy size to throw in your purse. Nice color. Can't beat the price of 6 bucks when everything else is sooo expensive!

reviews.headline: I will be buying again!
reviews.comments: Love this beautiful color and it's nice and moisturizing. It gives a nice shine to your lips.

reviews.headline: Very pretty
reviews.comments: Very pretty color that works well with a brown liner. Its also the perfect amount of shine without any chunky patches of glitter. The shine in the gloss also distributes evenly

reviews.headline: Try it!
reviews.comments: Non sticky, great shine and inexpensive! Highly recommend.

reviews.headline: Literally love it!
reviews.comments: This lipgloss is amazing! I got the shade rocky road and it's literallly the best color. It's classy and cute and great to reapply. Absolutely love it!

reviews.headline: Okay
reviews.comments: Have been using for years. Its an okay gloss. Have to apply many layers for colors to show.

reviews.headline: It has potential....
reviews.comments: It's okay. It's faintly gritty, and the glitter and pigment is bit patchy. I think the patchiness is a result of the applicator being very small and might apply better if the tube and applicator was wider. I guess you get what you pay for.

reviews.headline: changed Angel Food Cake
reviews.comments: Angel Food Cake was has been my favorite shade of lip gloss for so many years— a lightly pigmented, cool-toned mauvy pink. Well the last one I purchased expired, so I just bought a new one today. Now it's a much deeper shade (like magenta) and much more pigmented. It makes me look like a clown. Why change a shade instead of just making a brand new one? Back to searching for a dupe of the original shade.

reviews.headline: Very pretty
reviews.comments: This gloss if very pretty. Good color and coverage looks very pretty over a lip stain

reviews.headline: Great alternative to MAC lip gloss
reviews.comments: I found this gem many years back and have completely replaced all my MAC lip glosses. It's not as sticky, and goes on buttery smooth. I am taking one star away because it doesn't last as long as I would love. Otherwise, excellent for the price.

reviews.headline: tiny applicator
reviews.comments: I like the formula and pigmentation, but the applicator so small.

reviews.headline: It's a cute color!!
reviews.comments: It's sort of bright and not too subtle but the right amount makes an amazing lip combo.

reviews.headline: Favorite
reviews.comments: Nice inexpensive lip gloss

reviews.headline: Super glittery
reviews.comments: I got the color She Got Money and wow it is super pink and super glittery! Once it wipes away the glitter remains so then you just have very obvious glitter all over your lips. It's cute but not for everybody.

reviews.headline: Very nice
reviews.comments: Love this gloss

faceoff_positive.comments: First off let me say that I have fallen in love with NYX products. At first I was just looking for a gloss to keep in my purse. I now can say that with the exception of my foundation, every make up product I use is of the NYX brand. So of course, I would own the infamous Butter Gloss. Here's what I like about it: it's smooth, light and long lasting. I'm the kind of girl who lives her days from dawn to dusk and this gloss is perfect for me. Not only does it come in various shades, it is universal for everyone and lasts all day. My favorite by far is Maple Blondie. I thought it would be too pink for my skin and I worried that I chose the wrong color, but after using it I fell in love. This is my go to gloss for anything and everything. Whether it be a busy work day, date night or just a trip to the grocery store, this gloss is the perfect completion to any look. I highly recommend it!
faceoff_positive.headline: In Love With NYX

faceoff_negative.comments: This gloss is pretty cool. Its not too stick BUT you must exfoliate your lips first!!! The pigmentation of the gloss does not show up well on darker skin tones. I own Strawberry Parfait, very moisturizing.
